div.p:
With equal Justice hath Mr. Pope finely rallied another Species of these poring Wretches, the mere Medalists, who are wholly ignorant of the true use of those Coins which they seem so intensely to study, viz
With sharpen'd Sight pale Antiquaries pore,
Th' Inscription value, but the Rust adore;
This the Blue varnish, that the Green in
dears,
The sacred Rust of twice Two hundred Years.
To gain Pescennius one employs his Schemes;
One gains a Cecrops in exstatic Dreams;
Poor Vadius Dr. Woodward. long with learned Spleen devour'd
Can taste no Pleasure since his Shield was scour'd;
And Curio restless by the Fair-One's Side,
Sighs for an Otho, and neglects his Bride Pope's Verses to Mr. Addison, on his Dialogues upon Medals. .
